contentrichtext.text: '''[[Orestes]]''' was a figure in Greek mythology. '''Orestes''' or '''Orestis''' may also refer to: in '''drama''': * [[Orestes (play)|''Orestes'' (play)]], a tragedy by Euripides * ''[[Horestes]]'', a morality play by John Pickering * A character in the tragedy [[Electra (Sophocles)|''Electra'' (Sophocles)]] * A character in Aeschylus' trilogy of tragedies ''[[Oresteia]]'' in '''places''': * [[Orestes, Indiana]], United States * [[Orestis (region)]], in Upper Macedonia in '''watercraft''': * [[HMS Orestes|HMS ''Orestes'']], one of various British Royal Navy ships * [[USS Orestes (AGP-10)|USS ''Orestes'' (AGP-10)]], a United States Navy boat in '''other uses''': * [[Orestes (given name)]], and persons with the name * A song by A Perfect Circle on ''[[Mer de Noms]]'' {{disambig}}
